</table>"""
            paragraph table
        }

        section("<b>📈 Trends</b>") {
            paragraph "Trends use the same drain thresholds as Health. The difference is that Health is a long-term " +
                      "confidence-weighted average while Trend reacts to recent samples and can shift faster. " +
                      "A short spike may push the Trend to 🔴 Heavy Drain while Health stays 🟢 Good until enough samples confirm the pattern."
            def table = """<table style='width:100%; border-collapse: collapse;'>
<tr style='font-weight:bold;'><td>Trend</td><td>Drain Rate (per day)</td><td>Health Equivalent</td></tr>
<tr><td>🟢 Stable</td><td>&lt; 0.3%</td><td>Excellent</td></tr>
<tr><td>🟠 Moderate</td><td>0.3% – 0.8%</td><td>Good</td></tr>
<tr><td>🔴 Heavy Drain</td><td>0.8% – 1.5%</td><td>Fair — worth monitoring, no alert</td></tr>
<tr><td>🔴 Heavy Drain</td><td>&gt; 1.5%</td><td>Poor — High Drain alert fires</td></tr>
</table>"""
            paragraph table
        }

        section("<b>⏳ What Is 'Pending' Health?</b>") {
            paragraph "When a battery is new or has just been replaced, the app intentionally withholds a health verdict " +
                      "and shows <b>⏳ Pending</b> instead. This prevents false 'Poor' labels caused by sparse or noisy early readings.<br><br>" +
                      "Two conditions must both be met before a health rating is assigned:<br>" +
                      "• At least <b>5 drain samples</b> collected — shown as ⏳ Pending (X/5 samples) in the Health column of the Summary and Trends pages<br>" +
                      "• At least <b>5 days</b> since the battery was replaced or first seen<br><br>" +
                      "Once both gates pass, a confidence-weighted verdict is calculated from the real data. " +
                      "Samples accumulate from scheduled scans and device-triggered battery events — more frequent scans mean faster maturity."
        }

        section("<b>📊 How Confidence Weighting Works</b>") {
            paragraph "Even after the Pending gate clears, early readings carry less weight than established ones. " +
                      "The app blends the measured drain toward a safe default (0.30%/day) based on how many samples " +
                      "have been collected. With 5 samples the blend is partial; by 10 samples the full measured drain is used.<br><br>" +
                      "This means a single unusual reading cannot spike a device straight to 'Poor' — the verdict builds gradually " +
                      "as more real-world data arrives. Confidence is shown as a percentage in the Trends table."
        }

        section("<b>🔍 What Is Battery Drain?</b>") {
            paragraph "Drain shows how fast a device uses battery (% per day). Lower values mean longer battery life. " +
                      "Drain is calculated using EWMA (exponential weighted moving average) across the last 10 readings — " +
                      "recent readings matter slightly more than older ones, but a single spike won't throw off the average.<br><br>" +
                      "The <b>Scan Interval</b> setting controls how often the app actively reads each device to generate a new sample. " +
                      "Devices also contribute a sample automatically whenever they fire a battery event on their own. " +
                      "Scanning more frequently means health ratings mature faster."
        }

        section("<b>📅 Estimated Days Remaining</b>") {
            paragraph "Estimated days remaining = current battery level ÷ average daily drain. " +
                      "This is an approximation and works best once a device has 7+ days of history. " +
                      "Devices showing ⏳ Pending will have less reliable estimates until enough data is collected."
        }

        section("<b>🔁 Battery Replacement Detection</b>") {
            paragraph "Replacement is automatically detected when a device jumps from ≤40% up to ≥90–95%. " +
                      "If a battery is replaced before dropping to 40%, the jump may not meet the detection threshold — " +
                      "in that case, log it manually from the main page to keep trends accurate.<br><br>" +
                      "After any replacement (auto or manual), drain history resets, the device returns to ⏳ Pending, " +
                      "and the 'Recently Replaced' tag clears after 24 hours."
        }

        section("<b>⚠️ High Drain Alerts</b>") {
            paragraph "A High Drain alert fires when a device crosses into 🔴 Poor health territory — meaning its drain rate exceeds 1.5% per day. " +
                      "This threshold aligns with the Poor health boundary so the alert and the health rating always agree: " +
                      "if you see a High Drain alert, the device will also show 🔴 Poor in the Health column.<br><br>" +
                      "Devices rated 🟠 Fair (0.8–1.5%/day) are worth monitoring but do not trigger a High Drain alert — " +
                      "the Health and Trend columns reflect that elevated drain without generating extra noise."
        }

        section("<b>⏱ Stale Devices & Last Battery</b>") {
            paragraph "A device is <b>stale</b> if it has not reported any activity within the configured threshold (default: 24 hours). " +
                      "Stale is based on <b>Last Activity</b> — the last time the device communicated anything to the hub.<br><br>" +
                      "<b>Last Battery</b> is different — it shows the last time this app received a battery level reading for the device, " +
                      "either from a scheduled scan or a device-triggered battery event. Some devices only report their battery level " +
                      "infrequently (every few days, or only when the level actually changes), so Last Battery can appear much older " +
                      "than Last Activity even on a perfectly healthy device. This is normal and expected.<br><br>" +
                      "Stale devices are flagged in the summary and notifications. Check stale devices for connectivity issues."
        }

        section("<b>⚙️ Device Adjustments</b>") {
            paragraph "Locks, sensors, and contact devices report more frequently by nature. The app applies an adjusted " +
                      "drain calculation for these device types to avoid overestimating their drain rate."
        }

        section("<b>⚠ Troubleshooting High Drain</b>") {
            paragraph "If a device shows High Drain or Poor health after the Pending period:<br>" +
                      "• Check signal strength and mesh routing<br>" +
                      "• Verify reporting frequency in the device driver<br>" +
                      "• Confirm correct battery type in the Battery Catalog<br>" +
                      "• Consider environmental factors (temperature, distance)<br>" +
                      "• Review device firmware or driver settings<br><br>" +
                      "Note: devices that report very frequently (e.g. every few minutes) may show higher apparent drain " +
                      "because each report captures a small but real drop. Compare similar devices to spot outliers."
        }

        section("<b>💡 Tips for Best Results</b>") {
            paragraph "• Let new batteries run for at least a week before trusting health ratings<br>" +
                      "• Use the Battery Catalog to log battery types — this helps with replacement planning<br>" +
                      "• Consistent low drain over time = healthy, well-placed device<br>" +
                      "• Devices with very infrequent reporting (days between updates) will take longer to fill samples<br>" +
                      "• After replacing a battery, use Manual Replacement to reset the history immediately rather than " +
                      "waiting for auto-detection"
        }
    }
